{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dbb5b467-b5ac-4e9e-87c3-9d08fdee663e","content":"With .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform — **you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property was a bridge for .NET 9 and earlier to opt `dotnet test` into MTP. On .NET 10 SDK it's simply ignored.\n\nYou still need `EnableMSTestRunner` (it makes your test project an MTP executable). Let me clean up your csproj:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_1SpOnmQng7x3pKdvvAlOSs","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-b970878f90c64ba3a0787bd533c381a7/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-b970878f90c64ba3a0787bd533c381a7/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"eff69680-834f-47ab-8d4f-871bfb453de7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). They want to know about the native MTP support in .NET 10's `dotnet test`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. The new `dotnet test` in .NET 10 uses MTP by default.\n\nKey points:\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` has been rewritten to use Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively.\n\n\n2. `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` was a bridge property for earlier .NET versions to enable MTP support through `dotnet test`, but it's now redundant on .NET 10.\n3. `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required — it configures the MSTest runner and makes the test project executable with MTP.\n4. They should remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from their project file since it serves no purpose in .NET 10.","outputTokens":555},"id":"e833df13-77ea-46d9-9683-74d101eb95ab","timesta